WorldStage Newsonline– Academic staff of the Federal Polytechnic, Ado-Ekiti, have denied any involvement in the accusation that the rector, Dr Dayo Oladebeye, invested one billion naira staff salary in Bitcoin. The institution’s Director of Protocol, Information and Public Relations, Mr Ade Adeyemi-Adejoku, said in a statement on Wednesday that the teaching staff washed their hands off the allegation in a letter addressed to the rector on Tuesday. They sent the letter to the rector on the platform of the institution’s chapter of the Academic Staff Union of Polytechnics (ASUP), Adeyemi-Adejoku stated. A correspondent of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) gathered that the letter to the rector was written on the heels of mediation between the management and the teaching staff by the Ewi Ado-Ekiti, Oba Rufus Adejugbe, on Monday and Tuesday In another letter addressed to the rector, the union also expressed regret that its members staged a protest on Tuesday during which they locked the institution’s gate. The action prevented the students from writing their second semester examinations. Chairman of the institution’s ASUP chapter, Dr Olabisi Olasehinde, who signed the letter entitled: “Industrial face-off at the Federal Polytechnic Ado-Ekiti’’, noted that “the action is regretted with all sincerity’’.